# Runtime logging session - Phase 3

## Context
- Environment: container CLI without a full WordPress stack.
- Logger: `FPMultilanguage\Services\RuntimeLogger` hooked into PHP error handling and WordPress deprecation notices.

## Observations
- Instrumentation successfully registers on `plugins_loaded` and funnels PHP notices, warnings, and errors through the existing plugin logger store.
- Unable to reproduce admin or front-end requests because WordPress is not available in the execution environment. No runtime log entries were generated.

## Follow-up
- Re-run the runtime logger on a WordPress instance to capture actual admin/settings interactions.
- Confirm log persistence in the `fp_multilanguage_logs` option and export entries for later phases.
